@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<style>
    .privacy-wrapper {
        max-width: 720px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        animation: fadeSlideUp 0.6s ease both;
    }

    .privacy-header {
        text-align: center;
        margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    }

    .privacy-header .badge-label {
        display: inline-block;
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(0,201,167,0.2), rgba(108,99,255,0.2));
        border: 1px solid rgba(0,201,167,0.35);
        color: #00C9A7;
        font-size: 0.75rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        letter-spacing: 1.5px;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        padding: 0.3rem 0.9rem;
        border-radius: 50px;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .privacy-header h1 {
        font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.4rem);
        font-weight: 700;
        background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ffffff, #00C9A7);
        -webkit-background-clip: text;
        -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
        background-clip: text;
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }

    .privacy-header p {
        color: rgba(255,255,255,0.45);
        font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    .privacy-card {
        background: rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
        border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
        border-radius: 20px;
        padding: 2.5rem;
        backdrop-filter: blur(20px);
        -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(20px);
        box-shadow: 0 8px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.35), inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
        color: rgba(255,255,255,0.75);
        line-height: 1.8;
        font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    .privacy-card p {
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .privacy-card h2 {
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        font-weight: 600;
        color: #00C9A7;
        margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
    }

    .privacy-card h2:first-child {
        margin-top: 0;
    }

    .privacy-card ul {
        margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 1.25rem;
        padding: 0;
    }

    .privacy-card ul li {
        margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
        color: rgba(255,255,255,0.65);
    }

    .privacy-card .last-updated {
        display: inline-block;
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        color: rgba(255,255,255,0.3);
        margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
        padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
        border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
        border-radius: 50px;
        background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
    }

    @@keyframes fadeSlideUp {
        from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(20px); }
        to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
    }
</style>

<div class="privacy-wrapper">
    <div class="privacy-header">
        <div class="badge-label">Legal</div>
        <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
        <p>Transparency about how we handle your data.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="privacy-card">
        <span class="last-updated">Last updated: February 28, 2026</span>

        <h2>1. Overview</h2>
        <p>
            TextEditor ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy
            explains what information we collect when you use our web-based text editor, how we use it,
            and the choices you have. We believe in keeping things simple and transparent.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We collect only what is necessary to provide the service:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Editor content:</strong> Text you write or paste into the editor is stored locally in your browser session to power the Memento-based version history feature. It is not transmitted to our servers.</li>
            <li><strong>Version snapshots:</strong> Named snapshots you save are kept in browser memory for the duration of your session and are cleared when you close the tab.</li>
            <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> We may collect anonymised, aggregated analytics (e.g. page views, feature interactions) to improve the product. This data cannot be used to identify you.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Cookies &amp; Local Storage</h2>
        <p>
            TextEditor uses browser local storage solely to preserve your editing session across page refreshes.
            We do not use advertising cookies or third-party tracking cookies. You can clear local storage at
            any time through your browser settings, which will remove all stored content and snapshots.
        </p>

        <h2>4. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>Any information we collect is used only to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Operate and maintain the editor and version-history features.</li>
            <li>Diagnose technical problems and improve performance.</li>
            <li>Understand aggregate usage patterns to guide product development.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>We do not sell, rent, or share your data with third parties for marketing purposes.</p>

        <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
            Because editor content lives in your browser, <em>you</em> control how long it persists.
            Closing your browser tab clears all session data. Any anonymised analytics we retain are
            kept for no longer than 12 months before being deleted or further anonymised.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Security</h2>
        <p>
            We follow industry-standard practices to protect any data that passes through our systems,
            including encrypted connections (HTTPS). However, no method of transmission over the internet
            is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
            We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the
            "Last updated" date above. Continued use of TextEditor after changes are posted constitutes
            your acceptance of the revised policy.
        </p>

    </div>
</div>
